   "source": [
    "# BUS 696 Final Project: Expanded U.S. Equities Cross-Sectional Factor Strategy\n",
    "\n",
    "**Author:** Manuel Lara | Chapman University | BUS 696: Generative AI in Finance  \n",
    "**Due:** May 13, 2026  \n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Strategy Overview\n",
    "\n",
    "**Universe:** 200–300 large/mid-cap U.S. equities (S&P 500 / Russell 1000)  \n",
    "**Rebalancing:** Monthly cross-sectional ranking  \n",
    "**Model:** XGBoost for cross-sectional return prediction  \n",
    "\n",
    "### 5 Core Signals\n",
    "| # | Signal | Economic Hypothesis | Source |\n",
    "|---|--------|--------------------|---------|\n",
    "| 1 | Price Momentum (12-1m) | Jegadeesh & Titman (1993) underreaction | yfinance |\n",
    "| 2 | Insider Net-Buying Ratio | Private information (Form 4 P vs S) | SEC EDGAR |\n",
    "| 3 | Low Volatility Anomaly | Frazzini & Pedersen (2014) leverage constraints | yfinance |\n",
    "| 4 | Earnings Quality Composite | Richardson et al. (2005) accruals + buyback yield + revision | yfinance / EDGAR |\n",
    "| 5 | Macro Regime Filter | VIX + yield curve as portfolio scaler | FRED / yfinance |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Alt Data Bonus (+10):** LLM News Sentiment via Claude API — richer than raw Alpha Vantage scores  \n",
    "\n",
    "### Key Risk Controls\n",
    "- Half-Kelly sizing: `f* = IC / (1 - IC²) × 0.5`\n",
    "- Regime scaling: VIX < 20 → 100%, VIX 20–30 → 75%, VIX > 30 → 50%\n",
    "- ML transaction cost model (square root law + VIX spread)\n",
    "- Walk-forward validation: 60 monthly folds (2018–2024), min 36-month training window\n",
    "\n",
    "### Baselines\n",
    "1. Equal-weight buy-and-hold of universe  \n",
    "2. Pure 12-1 month momentum sort (no ML)"
   ]
  },
  {
