   "id": "6e44190f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Section 2: Signal Construction\n",
    "\n",
    "> **LOOK-AHEAD BIAS PREVENTION:** All signals are computed on information available at month-end t,  \n",
    "> predicting returns from month t+1. Accounting signals are lagged by one additional quarter  \n",
    "> to account for SEC filing delays (45 days for 10-Q, 60 days for 10-K)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "cb3848fd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Signal 1: Price Momentum (12-1 month)\n",
    "**Hypothesis:** Jegadeesh & Titman (1993) — stocks that outperformed over the past 12 months  \n",
    "(excluding the most recent month to avoid short-term reversal) continue to outperform.  \n",
    "**Economic mechanism:** Investor underreaction to gradual information arrival."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "ddec68be",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# Momentum = cumulative return from t-12 to t-1 (skip month t to avoid reversal)\n",
    "# Lag structure: use prices at t to compute signal; predict return at t+1\n",
    "\n",
    "def compute_momentum(prices_monthly, lookback=12, skip=1):\n",
    "    \"\"\"12-1 month momentum with skip-month reversal avoidance.\"\"\"\n",
    "    # Price at t-1 (skip month)\n",
    "    p_t1  = prices_monthly.shift(skip)\n",
    "    # Price at t-12\n",
    "    p_t12 = prices_monthly.shift(lookback)\n",
    "    mom = p_t1 / p_t12 - 1\n",
    "    return mom\n",
    "\n",
    "sig_momentum = compute_momentum(prices_monthly)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Cross-sectional z-score (rolling, prevents look-ahead in normalization)\n",
    "sig_momentum_z = sig_momentum.sub(sig_momentum.mean(axis=1), axis=0)\\\n",
    "                             .div(sig_momentum.std(axis=1), axis=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Momentum signal shape: {sig_momentum_z.shape}\")\n",
    "print(f\"Sample (2020-01): {sig_momentum_z.loc['2020-01-31'].dropna().describe()}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7ca054bd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Signal 2: Insider Net-Buying Ratio (SEC Form 4) — REFINED\n",
    "**Hypothesis:** Corporate insiders have private information about future earnings.  \n",
    "Open-market purchases (coded P) signal bullish views; sales (S) signal bearish.  \n",
    "**Refinement (FSM/DCF insight):** Filter Form 4 to Type P (open-market purchase) and Type S (open-market sale) only.  \n",
    "Exclude: type M (option exercise), F (disposition for tax), G (gift), H (intra-company transfer) — these are non-informational."
   ]
  },
